						               													<description>Quantum Shock is a scifi horror boardgame for 1 to 4 players with modular map tiles, cards, dice, amazing miniatures and a powerful narrative campaign. &amp;#10;Players can manipulate time and space, jump between dimensions, and learn all kind of weird skills, while fighting or hidding from the twisted horrors that will infest their reality.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can perform common actions like moving, searching for items or attack enemies. But they can also hide from enemies, teleport though portals or jump to unknown areas of the map.&amp;#10;The attack system uses a combination of dice roll and card decks, including intense fight with huge bosses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rotating the modular map tiles, players change between dimensions, finding new secrets and special items but also unlocking deadly menaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has a timeline that controls the turns of players and creatures. The characters can use their skills to manipulate time, adjusting this timeline and the events of the campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core game has a 10 episodes campaign, with an average time of 90 to 120 minutes each one. The main goal of the game is to return to your own dimension, as players are lost in time and space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All players and enemies are represented by highly detailed miniatures, including bosses and secondary characters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
